President Jacob Zuma is facing a fifth motion of no confidence in the National Assembly on Thursday.The latest motion, at the behest of the Democratic Alliance, comes a week after the release of former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela&#x2019;s report into allegations of state capture.While the &#x201C;State of Capture&#x201D; report has not assigned guilt to any party, it has raised a number of concerns about the relationship between high ranking politicialns and the influential Gupta family, who are close friends of the president.We asked political parties what their view are on Thursday&#x2019;s no confidence motion.IOL Mojo